{"id":"2102.10704","submitter":"Janos Pach","authors":"Peter Frankl and Janos Pach","title":"On well-connected sets of strings","comments":"6 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","abstract":"  Given $n$ pairwise disjoint sets $X_1,\\ldots, X_n$, we call the elements of\n$S=X_1\\times\\ldots\\times X_n$ strings. A nonempty set of strings $W\\subseteq S$\nis said to be well-connected if for every $v\\in W$ and for every $i\\, (1\\le\ni\\le n)$, there is another element $v'\\in W$ which differs from $v$ only in its\n$i$th coordinate. We prove a conjecture of Yaokun Wu and Yanzhen Xiong by\nshowing that every set of more than $\\prod_{i=1}^n|X_i|-\\prod_{i=1}^n(|X_i|-1)$\nstrings has a well-connected subset. This bound is tight.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 21 Feb 2021 22:29:50 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 21 Dec 2021 15:33:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-22"}
