{"id":"2102.11927","submitter":"Rub\\'en Cape\\'ans","authors":"Gaspar Alfaro, Rub\\'en Cape\\'ans and Miguel A.F.Sanju\\'an","title":"Forcing the escape: Partial control of escaping orbits from a transient\n  chaotic region","comments":"9 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.DS nlin.CD","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  A new control algorithm based on the partial control method has been\ndeveloped. The general situation we are considering is an orbit starting in a\ncertain phase space region Q having a chaotic transient behavior affected by\nnoise, so that the orbit will definitely escape from Q in an unpredictable\nnumber of iterations. Thus, the goal of the algorithm is to control in a\npredictable manner when to escape. While partial control has been used as a way\nto avoid escapes, here we want to adapt it to force the escape in a controlled\nmanner. We have introduced new tools such as escape functions and escape sets\nthat once computed makes the control of the orbit straightforward. We have\napplied the new idea to three different cases in order to illustrate the\nvarious application possibilities of this new algorithm.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 21 Feb 2021 16:21:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-02-25"}
